  "descriptionText": "HEESEN PLEASURE VESSEL for sale 1985 | 4 Guest cabins + 5 Crew Beds | Tax Not PaidWith low Engine Hours (280 hours)The HEESEN PLEASURE VESSEL for sale 1985 presents a unique opportunity to acquire a 31.85-metre motor yacht, representing the distinctive craftsmanship and robust construction of the renowned Heesen shipyard. Maintained in good condition throughout her lifespan, the vessel has benefited from a thorough refit in 2023, ensuring her systems and accommodation are up to date for new owners.Fully Equipped (Autopilot, Radar, Generator, Inverter, Bow & Stern Thruster, Water Maker, AC, Dishwasher, Washing Machine, Dryer, Underwater Lights...)Specification and Equipment List:GeneralBuilder: Heesen YachtsModel: Pleasure VesselYear: 1985Refit: 2023Overall Length: 31.85 mBeam: 6.27 mMaximum Draft: 3.06 mWeight: 140,000 kgFuel Tank: 15,000 LFresh Water Tank: 1,800 LWaste Water Tank: 750 LGrey Water Tank: 750 LEnginesNumber: 2Brand: Detroit Diesel 8122-7400Engine Power: 1,045 hp eachEngine Hours: 280Transmission: ShaftMaximum Speed: 12 knotsCruising Speed: 10 knotsFuel Type: DieselBow Thruster and Stern ThrusterStabilisation and HandlingStabiliser Model: FIN StabilisersHydraulic GangwayJoystick ControlExternal Equipment LayoutService Boat Equipment, with Launching System and GarageHardtop sun protectionTeak Cockpit and Side DeckUnderwater LightingSun BedsCockpit Cushions, Cockpit AwningSeabob for water activitiesInterior EquipmentCabins: 4Double Beds: 3Single Beds: 1Crew Cabins: 5 bedsBathrooms/Toilets: 2Air ConditioningGalley appliances: Refrigerator, Freezer, Oven, Ice Maker, Wine Cooler, Dishwasher, Washing Machine, DryerWater Maker for extended cruisingElectronicsVoltage: Standard yacht systems (24V/220V)Battery Charger, InverterGenerator Quantity: 2Generator Model: Onan 40kWGenerator Hours: 811Satellite AntennaRadar, Chart Plotter, Autopilot with Repeat UnitsVHF RadioDepth Gauge, Speed Gauge, Chain CounterTV Antenna, TV in living/social areasAdditional FeaturesBoat is fitted with stabilisers for added comfort underwayHydraulic equipment for easier handling and boardingBroad range of exterior relaxation areasThis HEESEN PLEASURE VESSEL for sale 1985 is ready for immediate use following her 2023 refit, offering a solid platform for extensive cruising. Her technical and interior updates ensure reliable cruising and enjoyable time onboard. Inspection is recommended for those seeking a vessel combining classic style with up-to-date systems, in good condition.For further information or to arrange a viewing, please contact the broker.",
  "descriptionHtml": "<h4 style=\"text-align: center\"><strong>HEESEN PLEASURE VESSEL for sale 1985 | 4 Guest cabins + 5 Crew Beds | Tax Not Paid</strong></h4><p style=\"text-align: center\"><em><u>With low Engine Hours (280 hours)</u></em></p><p id=\"isPasted\">The&nbsp;<strong>HEESEN PLEASURE VESSEL for sale 1985</strong>&nbsp;presents a unique opportunity to acquire a 31.85-metre motor yacht, representing the distinctive craftsmanship and robust construction of the renowned Heesen shipyard. Maintained in good condition throughout her lifespan, the vessel has benefited from a thorough <span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"><strong>refit in 2023</strong></span>, ensuring her systems and accommodation are up to date for new owners.</p><p><em><u>Fully Equipped (Autopilot, Radar, Generator, Inverter, Bow &amp; Stern Thruster, Water Maker, AC, Dishwasher, Washing Machine, Dryer, Underwater Lights...)</u></em></p><p><strong>Specification and Equipment List:</strong></p><p><strong>General</strong></p><ul><li>Builder: Heesen Yachts</li><li>Model: Pleasure Vessel</li><li>Year: 1985</li><li>Refit: 2023</li><li>Overall Length: 31.85 m</li><li>Beam: 6.27 m</li><li>Maximum Draft: 3.06 m</li><li>Weight: 140,000 kg</li><li>Fuel Tank: 15,000 L</li><li>Fresh Water Tank: 1,800 L</li><li>Waste Water Tank: 750 L</li><li>Grey Water Tank: 750 L</li></ul><p><strong>Engines</strong></p><ul><li>Number: 2</li><li>Brand: Detroit Diesel 8122-7400</li><li>Engine Power: 1,045 hp each</li><li>Engine Hours: 280</li><li>Transmission: Shaft</li><li>Maximum Speed: 12 knots</li><li>Cruising Speed: 10 knots</li><li>Fuel Type: Diesel</li><li>Bow Thruster and Stern Thruster</li></ul><p><strong>Stabilisation and Handling</strong></p><ul><li>Stabiliser Model: FIN Stabilisers</li><li>Hydraulic Gangway</li><li>Joystick Control</li></ul><p><strong>External Equipment Layout</strong></p><ul><li>Service Boat Equipment, with Launching System and Garage</li><li>Hardtop sun protection</li><li>Teak Cockpit and Side Deck</li><li>Underwater Lighting</li><li>Sun Beds</li><li>Cockpit Cushions, Cockpit Awning</li><li>Seabob for water activities</li></ul><p><strong>Interior Equipment</strong></p><ul><li>Cabins: 4</li><li>Double Beds: 3</li><li>Single Beds: 1</li><li>Crew Cabins: 5 beds</li><li>Bathrooms/Toilets: 2</li><li>Air Conditioning</li><li>Galley appliances: Refrigerator, Freezer, Oven, Ice Maker, Wine Cooler, Dishwasher, Washing Machine, Dryer</li><li>Water Maker for extended cruising</li></ul><p><strong>Electronics</strong></p><ul><li>Voltage: Standard yacht systems (24V/220V)</li><li>Battery Charger, Inverter</li><li>Generator Quantity: 2</li><li>Generator Model: Onan 40kW</li><li>Generator Hours: 811</li><li>Satellite Antenna</li><li>Radar, Chart Plotter, Autopilot with Repeat Units</li><li>VHF Radio</li><li>Depth Gauge, Speed Gauge, Chain Counter</li><li>TV Antenna, TV in living/social areas</li></ul><p><strong>Additional Features</strong></p><ul><li>Boat is fitted with stabilisers for added comfort underway</li><li>Hydraulic equipment for easier handling and boarding</li><li>Broad range of exterior relaxation areas</li></ul><p>This&nbsp;<strong>HEESEN PLEASURE VESSEL for sale 1985</strong>&nbsp;is ready for immediate use following her 2023 refit, offering a solid platform for extensive cruising. Her technical and interior updates ensure reliable cruising and enjoyable time onboard. Inspection is recommended for those seeking a vessel combining classic style with up-to-date systems, in good condition.</p><p>For further information or to arrange a viewing, please contact the broker.</p>",
